"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The use of `apply` with a lambda function on a groupby object is incorrect because the result of `apply` is a Series with a different index than the original DataFrame. The `reset_index(drop=True)` is not applied correctly to the result of the `apply` method, which can lead to misalignment of the indices.\",\n  \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(drop=True)\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(level=0, drop=True)\"\n}"